<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[835,1444,1537,1922]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">
was originally described from Black Mountain, 
<collectingRegion box="[1214,1393,1574,1598]" country="United States of America" name="North Carolina" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">North Carolina</collectingRegion>
and has been reported from adjacent states of 
<collectingRegion country="United States of America" name="South Carolina" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">South Carolina</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1015,1136,1646,1669]" country="United States of America" name="Tennessee" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">Tennessee</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Unzicker &amp; McCaskill" firstAuthor="Unzicker" pageId="6" pageNumber="36" refId="ref12178" refString="Unzicker, J. D. &amp; V. H. McCaskill. 1982. Plecoptera. Pp. 5.1 - 5.50. In: Aquatic insects and oligochaetes of North and South Carolina. A. R. Brigham, W. U. Brigham &amp; A. Gnilka (Eds.) Midwest Aquatic Enterprises, Mahomet, Illinois." type="book" year="1982">Unzicker &amp; McCaskill 1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Stark" box="[912,1127,1682,1706]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Stark" pageId="6" pageNumber="36" pagination="383 - 397" refId="ref11694" refString="Stark, B. P., S. W. Szczytko &amp; R. W. Baumann. 1986. North American stoneflies (Plecoptera): systematics, distribution, and taxonomic references. Great Basin Naturalist, 46: 383 - 397. https: // www. jstor. org / stable / pdf / 41712245. pdf" type="journal article" year="1986">Stark et al. 1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kondratieff, B. C. &amp; C. H. Nelson" box="[1148,1436,1681,1706]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36" pagination="596 - 602" refId="ref10123" refString="Kondratieff, B. C. &amp; C. H. Nelson. 1995. A review of the genus Remenus Ricker (Plecoptera: Perlodidae), with the description of two new species. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 97 (3): 596 - 602." type="journal article" year="1995">Kondratieff et al. 1995</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Stewart, K. W. &amp; B. P. Stark" box="[835,1100,1718,1742]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36" refId="ref11865" refString="Stewart, K. W. &amp; B. P. Stark. 2002. Nymphs of North American stonefly genera (Plecoptera). University of North Texas Press (reprint). 400 pp." type="book" year="2002">Stewart &amp; Stark 2002</bibRefCitation>
). This species was collected from the 
<typeStatus box="[940,992,1754,1778]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nelson &amp; Kondratieff, 1995 Kondratieff &amp; Nelson" authorityYear="1995" box="[1118,1310,1754,1778]" class="Insecta" family="Perlodidae" genus="Remenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duffieldi">
<emphasis box="[1118,1310,1754,1778]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">Remenus duffieldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1354,1373,1754,1768]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">nd</superScript>
order stream in the Blue Ridge Physiographic Province of 
<collectingRegion box="[835,932,1826,1850]" country="United States of America" name="Georgia" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">Georgia</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
